title: For Sale:  5.56 Lake City XM855 62gr. FMJ Penetrator Ammo 1,000 rounds
postcontent:
This is 5.56 Lake City XM855 62gr. Full Metal Jacket, Green Tip Penetrator, Federal Premium ammo from the Lake City factory. It is loaded to Military specifications and this particular load is the 62 grain Steel Penetrator with the painted green tip for easy identification. It is first run quality non-corrosive, boxer primed, re-loadable brass cases.
It is headstamped 2012 and it comes packed loose.

This is not the normal .223 55 grain associated with the American Eagle brand.  It is the higher grade military penetrator ammo.  This round has the potential to punch holes through steel plates. The price is below market average for this type, so don't try to convince me that you can get the 62 grain Penetrator for same price as 55 grain somewhere else.

Price is for 1,000 rounds, loose in the box. I am willing to break up the batch at 500 rounds, but nothing less. Basically .50 per round. Market is averaging at .54 per round.

Muzzle velocity: 3104 fps
Muzzle energy: 1326 ft/lbs
Uses: Personal Protection or Self Defense

Note: This item is manufactured in the Lake City Plant currently run by Federal ATK. The ammo is brand new, brass cased, boxer primed, non-corrosive and re-loadable. It is made to military specifications which require the cases to be annealed. Unlike civilian production ammo, the military requires to see evidence of annealing on the round itself. This is why the cases will appear to be discolored. This is done on purpose in order to meet the military requirement for overall strength and durability of the finished round.
